{
 "name": "RPlog_Accepting_Help",
 "title": "Accepting Help in the Forest Clearing",
 "summary": "In a secluded forest clearing on Caspar, the Jedi Master Kyyel sits brooding over a pair of silver wings when the silver-haired Jessalyn slips silently from the shadows to speak with him before her departure. She apologizes for dragging him into her troubles, and he gently renews his offer to help, revealing he owns a fast ship and would gladly take her wherever she needs to go. As the conversation turns to the Jedi Code and the questions stirred in him by his late mother's dying words, Jessalyn warns him not to trust her, confessing that a darkness has overtaken her and that her career as a Jedi Teacher may be over before it began. Kyyel counters that giving up on herself will only let that darkness grow, and that Master Skywalker's evident trust in her must count for something. Unable to commit, Jessalyn promises only to find him again if she must, and as night deepens over the planet Kyyel presses a comm frequency upon her so she can reach him, bidding her to stay safe.",
